1
00:00:29,291 --> 00:00:31,291
[GENKAKU]
Just your standard uber-monk...

2
00:00:31,375 --> 00:00:33,208
I'm concerned for your soul... 

3
00:00:33,291 --> 00:00:36,708
How it's stuck... in that
meat-sack of a body... 

4
00:00:36,791 --> 00:00:39,666
Whaddya say I let it out?

5
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:42,541
[GANTA] Whaddya say
I kick your ass?!

6
00:00:44,375 --> 00:00:46,250
[GANTA YELLS]

7
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:49,208
Go, Ganta...
Run away...!

8
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:53,625
[GUITAR SOUNDS]

9
00:00:56,625 --> 00:00:59,541
Down for a duet,
'cause I'm ready to shred!

10
00:00:59,625 --> 00:01:01,541
[GUITAR FEEDBACK]

11
00:01:05,666 --> 00:01:08,833
Get ready for some
rock'n roll, bitches!

12
00:01:10,250 --> 00:01:11,250
Huh...?

13
00:01:19,541 --> 00:01:21,958
[SHIRO]
Special attack...

14
00:01:22,041 --> 00:01:26,125
Ultra Chaos Endorphin
Screw Hadouken-style

15
00:01:26,208 --> 00:01:28,625
Alpha Version Kick!

16
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:31,541
Who...
the fuck... is she?

17
00:01:31,625 --> 00:01:33,666
Wait, why do I
know that attack?

18
00:01:33,750 --> 00:01:35,458
[SHIRO LAUGHS]

19
00:01:37,291 --> 00:01:40,041
Never fear! Aceman is here!

20
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:41,791
Hell yeah!

21
00:01:41,875 --> 00:01:45,291
[YOH THINKING]
Thank god. We're saved.

22
00:01:45,375 --> 00:01:47,500
If she doesn't
decide to kill us all.

23
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:50,333
Ganta! Look what
I got us for noms!

24
00:01:50,416 --> 00:01:52,458
Huh...?

25
00:01:52,541 --> 00:01:54,916
[GENKAKU]
Way to shit on my music...

26
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,541
S'all good; it'll wait
for another time.

27
00:01:57,625 --> 00:01:59,750
I'm a real patient guy.

28
00:02:03,041 --> 00:02:04,041
Huh...?

29
00:02:09,125 --> 00:02:14,125
♪ opening song ♪

30
00:03:39,291 --> 00:03:40,875
Mmmmm!

31
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:45,750
[SHIRO GIGGLES]

32
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:51,416
[GANTA THINKING]
What was with my power just now?

33
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:53,416
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

34
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,458
[ROKURO]
I miss a party?

35
00:03:55,541 --> 00:03:59,625
Yeah. Sorry...
It was hot... Well?

36
00:03:59,708 --> 00:04:01,625
Look at what daddy
got his hands on.

37
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:03,000
[KARAKO] Kick ass!

38
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:04,541
You're officially a god!

39
00:04:04,625 --> 00:04:07,958
Well... a minor demigod
of security loopholes, sure.

40
00:04:08,041 --> 00:04:10,708
We can put our money
where our mouth is now.

41
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:12,500
[ROKURO]
We runnin' a daycare?

42
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:14,916
[SHIRO] Hungry?

43
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,666
If you want some,
you better hurry up.

44
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:18,958
[GANTA] Hey, half of
that's supposed to me mine!

45
00:04:19,041 --> 00:04:20,500
Seriously, though:

46
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:23,583
where do you keep finding that
kind of pudding around here?

47
00:04:23,666 --> 00:04:25,666
The food court only sells
their in-house stuff,

48
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:27,208
as far as I know.

49
00:04:27,291 --> 00:04:29,875
[SHIRO] There's not one waiting
by your bed when you get up?

50
00:04:29,958 --> 00:04:30,875
No...

51
00:04:30,958 --> 00:04:32,250
These are the
prospective noobs.

52
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:34,416
Well, yeah.
The boy definitely is.

53
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:37,458
We were just about to introduce
him to the rest of the family.

54
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:38,708
Huh...

55
00:04:38,791 --> 00:04:41,333
[SHIRO AND GANTA
MAKE EATING SOUNDS]

56
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:43,541
Ah... that guy...

57
00:04:44,458 --> 00:04:50,583
[GROUP MURMURS]

58
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:52,250
Very pleased to
meet all of you...

59
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,791
My name's
Ganta Igarashi.

60
00:04:53,875 --> 00:04:55,291
[ENDOU] Hey, not to
be rude, half pint...

61
00:04:55,375 --> 00:04:57,958
But is that like
your old lady or what?

62
00:04:58,041 --> 00:05:03,166
[GANTA] Huh? No!
She's just a friend.

63
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:04,166
[KOUMOTO]
Your other friend's

64
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:05,791
the Hummingbird's
brother, right?

65
00:05:05,875 --> 00:05:07,791
[GANTA]
Yeah, that's Yoh...

66
00:05:07,875 --> 00:05:09,125
But he doesn't have
the Deadman virus

67
00:05:09,208 --> 00:05:11,125
like his little sister does.

68
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:12,500
[GROUP GASPS]

69
00:05:12,583 --> 00:05:14,333
So what the hell was
he doing in G-block?

70
00:05:14,416 --> 00:05:16,416
Uh, well it's kind of
a long story, actually...

71
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:17,583
[ROKURO]
Come on, guys.

72
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:20,083
Now's not the time
for twenty questions.

73
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:24,583
I can't concentrate
with all the damn noise. 

74
00:05:24,666 --> 00:05:27,875
Allow me to introduce
Bundou Rokuro... 

75
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:29,541
The chain's lifeline...

76
00:05:29,625 --> 00:05:32,250
He single-handedly
gathers most of our intel...

77
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:33,458
The stunt that
saved Hummingbird 

78
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:36,375
from the chopping block
was his brainchild.

79
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:40,625
Wow... Thanks, man.

80
00:05:40,708 --> 00:05:42,333
That's was
really awesome.

81
00:05:44,041 --> 00:05:45,541
Hey, be nice...

82
00:05:45,625 --> 00:05:48,625
His friend here spared us all
Genkaku's musical stylings...

83
00:05:48,708 --> 00:05:50,250
If we judge a man by
the company he keeps,

84
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:51,625
I'd say he's good stock.

85
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:53,041
[ENDOU LAUGHS]

86
00:05:53,125 --> 00:05:54,750
There's nobody you won't
give the benefit of the doubt.

87
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:56,916
And we've done
pretty damn well by it.

88
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,083
Yeah, maybe so...

89
00:05:58,166 --> 00:05:59,458
I mean, sure,
the kid might railroad us,

90
00:05:59,541 --> 00:06:01,833
but I think we're all
willing to give him a shot.

91
00:06:01,916 --> 00:06:03,333
Heh, guys...

92
00:06:03,416 --> 00:06:04,416
I hate to break
it to you,

93
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,166
but it wasn't
a compliment, Nag.

94
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:08,208
I... didn't really
think it was.

95
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:11,666
[GROUP LAUGHS]

96
00:06:13,541 --> 00:06:16,458
[NAGI] We've got coarse,
green and brown rice tea...

97
00:06:16,541 --> 00:06:17,958
What's your poison?

98
00:06:18,041 --> 00:06:20,375
I... don't want poison.

99
00:06:20,458 --> 00:06:22,250
He means do
you want anything.

100
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:26,125
Oh... well that's easy!
I want snacks all day long!

101
00:06:26,208 --> 00:06:29,541
Also... I want that big
shiny circle thing outside!

102
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:33,375
Hmm... Speaking
in riddles, I see.

103
00:06:34,875 --> 00:06:37,083
Oh, wow!

104
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:39,333
[KOSUGI] You're not
from gen. pop., are you?

105
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:41,333
Not that it's any
of my concern... 

106
00:06:41,416 --> 00:06:44,291
I was just wondering
how you three managed.

107
00:06:44,375 --> 00:06:47,791
I've been here longer
than anyone else has.

108
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:53,625
Dude, really, just
save yourself the time.

109
00:06:53,708 --> 00:06:55,416
[GANTA] Don't take this
the wrong way, but:

110
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,250
kind of laid back
bunch you got here...

111
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,833
I mean, you guys are plotting
a rebellion, aren't you?

112
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:01,500
[NAGI] Heh...

113
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:04,083
We have to pick our battles.

114
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:06,416
The situation
is serious enough.

115
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,750
I just figured
they'd be more...

116
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:11,125
[NAGI] Grim?

117
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:13,250
Does freedom look like
that to you, Ganta?

118
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:15,000
Something harsh?

119
00:07:21,458 --> 00:07:23,500
[KASUGA]
An inspection?

120
00:07:23,583 --> 00:07:25,333
Have you never
seen one done?

121
00:07:25,416 --> 00:07:26,458
[KASUGA]
No ma'am.

122
00:07:26,541 --> 00:07:28,583
Deadman Wonderland
is fully privatized.

123
00:07:28,666 --> 00:07:30,291
Meaning it's subject
to an annual,

124
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:32,500
week-long federal
safety inspection

125
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:34,958
by outside personnel.

126
00:07:35,041 --> 00:07:37,041
[MAKINA] Meaning the oily
little son of a bitch will be

127
00:07:37,125 --> 00:07:39,250
too busy glad-handing
bureaucrats to keep

128
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:41,791
a close eye on his
personal records.

129
00:07:41,875 --> 00:07:44,833
You mean we're going to
steal them... Which is a crime.

130
00:07:44,916 --> 00:07:47,041
Finding out what he
knows is our only hope

131
00:07:47,125 --> 00:07:50,375
of restoring order to this
place... Understood?

132
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:53,250
[KARAKO] There'll be no
performances that week,

133
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:57,125
public or private, so it'll
be our best window to act.

134
00:07:57,208 --> 00:07:59,458
And the top brass'll be too
busy plate-spinning trying to

135
00:07:59,541 --> 00:08:00,708
convince government inspectors

136
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:03,083
Deadman Wonderland
is on the up and up.

137
00:08:03,166 --> 00:08:05,791
[NAGI] That's
our point of attack.

138
00:08:05,875 --> 00:08:09,916
Our first and last
gamble, if you like.

139
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,833
The jailbreak to
end all jailbreaks.

140
00:08:12,916 --> 00:08:14,625
A mass exodus of Deadmen.

141
00:08:14,708 --> 00:08:16,041
[GANTA GASPS]

142
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:18,208
How you figure we're gonna
deal with the Undertakers?

143
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:20,958
We don't have a chance in hell
unless we can fend them off.

144
00:08:21,041 --> 00:08:22,375
[KARAKO] Exactly.

145
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:23,666
Undertakers...?

146
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:26,375
Mm-Hmm...
Therein lies the rub.

147
00:08:26,458 --> 00:08:29,250
You crossed paths with
one of their rank earlier.

148
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:33,500
They're chosen from
the prison's worst element;

149
00:08:33,583 --> 00:08:36,500
the sociopaths,
the irredeemable.

150
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:37,958
Run them through
a specialized

151
00:08:38,041 --> 00:08:39,791
"correctional" program...

152
00:08:39,875 --> 00:08:44,458
And poof... You've created
Tamaki's elite personal Gestapo.

153
00:08:44,541 --> 00:08:48,166
Anti-Deadmen.
The Undertakers.

154
00:08:49,375 --> 00:08:51,416
Man, that's
pretty messed up...

155
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,166
Wait, that explains everything!

156
00:08:53,250 --> 00:08:55,000
That's why my
Branch of Sin got owned!

157
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:56,416
[GROUP] Huh...?

158
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:58,500
Yeah, I'm kind of
not following you there...

159
00:08:58,583 --> 00:08:59,541
Dude, are you
talking about that

160
00:08:59,625 --> 00:09:01,333
wicked fighting
style they all use?

161
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:03,125
[ROKURO]
He means this...

162
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:04,541
Take a look at the
piece of footage

163
00:09:04,625 --> 00:09:07,500
I just hacked off the
surveillance network...

164
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:08,666
It's invaluable
when it comes to

165
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:11,416
doing homework on
prospective noobs.

166
00:09:16,541 --> 00:09:17,708
Huh?

167
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:21,458
[KOUMOTO]
Whatever, he just dodged you.

168
00:09:21,541 --> 00:09:22,708
[GANTA GRUNTS ANGRILY]

169
00:09:22,791 --> 00:09:24,416
Don't scare use
like that, man!

170
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,666
Next time, don't try to
fight while you're drunk.

171
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:28,125
[MIYAKO]
You're the one to talk?

172
00:09:28,208 --> 00:09:30,291
[GROUP LAUGHS]

173
00:09:30,375 --> 00:09:34,750
That's wrong...
That isn't what went down!

174
00:09:35,958 --> 00:09:37,250
Buck up...

175
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:40,125
When you're caught in a lie
deal with it like a man.

176
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:41,666
Seriously though, Nagi.

177
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:44,166
He's a snot-nosed,
ankle-biting little shit.

178
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:47,000
Even if we could trust him,
he'd be useless to the cause.

179
00:09:47,083 --> 00:09:48,208
Hey, lay off him, man...

180
00:09:48,291 --> 00:09:50,291
It's not like the kid
did anything to you.

181
00:09:50,375 --> 00:09:51,416
[GANTA GRUNTS ANGRILY]

182
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,583
[SHIRO]
What's the matter?

183
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:54,916
[GANTA]
For the record...

184
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,166
I haven't agreed to be
part of your little club.

185
00:09:57,250 --> 00:09:58,500
Woah, what
the hell, kid?

186
00:09:58,583 --> 00:10:01,250
You're more like a social
club than a rebellion.

187
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:04,250
The fact is, I wouldn't trust
you to make breakfast...

188
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:07,250
let alone pull
a friggin' jailbreak!

189
00:10:09,291 --> 00:10:11,291
Okay, I'm outta here...

190
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:13,583
Come on, Shiro.

191
00:10:13,666 --> 00:10:16,000
[SHIRO]
Oh... Okay.

192
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:19,791
That's
yours to keep.

193
00:10:19,875 --> 00:10:20,875
Ah...!

194
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:27,625
Stop being mean to Ganta.

195
00:10:28,208 --> 00:10:29,666
What now?

196
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:31,125
[NAGI SIGHS]

197
00:10:35,666 --> 00:10:38,000
[TAMAKI]
Yes, yes. Perfect.

198
00:10:39,625 --> 00:10:43,875
What this dungeon needs
is a little splash of whimsy.

199
00:10:43,958 --> 00:10:46,541
Let the clarions ring out!

200
00:10:50,958 --> 00:10:53,458
Today is one for
the history books.

201
00:11:00,375 --> 00:11:02,166
[TAMAKI SIGHS]

202
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:05,750
From this point forward...
I'm king of the hill.

203
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:12,291
[LOUD THUDS]

204
00:11:12,375 --> 00:11:14,541
[SENJI]
Undertakers? Sure.

205
00:11:14,625 --> 00:11:15,833
What do you want
to know about 'em?

206
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:18,750
[GANTA] Can they... 
neutralize Branch of Sin?

207
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:21,041
Like... Split up
one of my shots?

208
00:11:21,125 --> 00:11:25,625
What? Your little missiles
are serious shit, dude...

209
00:11:25,708 --> 00:11:27,375
But, they're blood, so...

210
00:11:27,458 --> 00:11:29,041
'Kay, not "split,"...

211
00:11:29,125 --> 00:11:32,250
But, maybe just make one
of 'em disappear, like...

212
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:35,833
I dunno... I could've
just been seein' things.

213
00:11:35,916 --> 00:11:37,416
[FABRIC TEARS]

214
00:11:38,458 --> 00:11:40,541
[SENJI] Are you tellin'
me you went head to head

215
00:11:40,625 --> 00:11:42,541
with a goddamn Undertaker?!

216
00:11:42,625 --> 00:11:44,375
Uh...
Well, yeah...

217
00:11:44,458 --> 00:11:45,958
You little fuck...

218
00:11:46,041 --> 00:11:47,916
What the hell's
wrong with you?!

219
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,000
Think you can
just square off

220
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,708
with whoever you
damn well please?!

221
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:53,500
You don't get to fight
'less I get front row!

222
00:11:53,583 --> 00:11:55,250
I... totally
didn't mean to!

223
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:56,750
Give me details.

224
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:59,583
Uh, well I... ran into
a girl named Karako

225
00:11:59,666 --> 00:12:01,375
and she took me to Nagi...

226
00:12:01,458 --> 00:12:05,041
Nagi, huh...?
Oh, y'mean the Owl.

227
00:12:05,125 --> 00:12:06,125
Now there's a guy with

228
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:08,208
an axe to grind 'gainst
the Undertakers.

229
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:11,125
[GANTA] Huh...?
What's his story?

230
00:12:11,208 --> 00:12:14,250
Heh. Why are you
so hard up to know?

231
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:15,625
I'm not...

232
00:12:15,708 --> 00:12:18,208
Just kinda of curious 'bout
where he's comin' from.

233
00:12:18,291 --> 00:12:19,916
Comin' from...?

234
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,875
Two years ago they killed
the poor bastard's wife.

235
00:12:22,958 --> 00:12:24,458
[GANTA GASPS]

236
00:12:26,791 --> 00:12:28,541
[SENJI] The higher ups
set 'em against each other

237
00:12:28,625 --> 00:12:30,791
during Carnival Corpse.

238
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:35,708
Word is he pleaded with Tamaki
to let him throw the fight...

239
00:12:35,791 --> 00:12:38,833
During "Too Bad
for the Loser"...

240
00:12:38,916 --> 00:12:41,666
They ripped out
his vocal chords.

241
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:44,500
Tamaki turned around on
'em both afterwards and

242
00:12:44,583 --> 00:12:46,083
punished the wife
for letting herself

243
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:48,333
be part of a fixed game...

244
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:51,208
Nagi tried to run
away with her, but...

245
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:58,166
He couldn't even cry her name
as she was bleeding to death

246
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:00,000
in his arms.

247
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:09,666
Oh... I hope
